Telco Customer Churn Analysis Report
Author: Ede Stan. C.
Role: Data Analyst / Business Analyst
Tools Used: Python, Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Google Colab
Project Type: Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) & Customer Churn Analysis

Executive Summary

Customer churn remains a significant challenge for telecommunication companies, as
losing customers negatively impacts revenue and increases the cost of acquiring new
customers. This project analyzes a telecom customer dataset to identify the key factors
associated with customer churn and provide actionable recommendations to improve
customer retention.
Using Python and data analysis libraries, the dataset was cleaned, explored, and
visualized to uncover trends in customer demographics, service usage, contract types,
payment methods, and customer tenure. The analysis revealed that customers with
short tenure, month-to-month contracts, and higher monthly charges were more likely
to churn.
The insights generated from this project can help organizations design targeted
retention strategies and improve customer loyalty.

1. Business Problem

Customer churn is costly for businesses because replacing lost customers often
requires significant marketing and acquisition expenses. Understanding the
characteristics of customers who are likely to leave enables organizations to implement
proactive retention strategies.
This project addresses the following business questions:
Which customers are most likely to churn?
Does customer tenure influence churn?
How does contract type affect retention?
Do higher monthly charges increase churn?
Which payment methods are associated with higher churn?

2. Project Objectives

The objectives of this analysis were to:
Clean and preprocess the customer dataset.
Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA).
Analyze customer churn patterns.
Segment customers by tenure.
Identify key drivers of churn.
Develop business recommendations based on the findings.

3. Dataset Overview

The dataset contains customer information, including:
• Customer ID
• Gender
• Senior Citizen status
• Partner and Dependents
